This paper deals with the randomised query complexity of a composition of a relation and a promise function, which is a topic in computational complexity theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the study of relations and promise functions, which are fundamental concepts in computer science, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves information theory, as it deals with the complexity of communication protocols, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a likely sub-category. The paper also involves lower bounds and tightness results, which are common in machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves cryptography, as it deals with the complexity of randomised algorithms, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a possible sub-category.
